name: framework/dataManager/DataManager.js
BasicHandler
description:
The BasicHandler implements a trap for the get method. It checks whether the
property is a function, and if it is it inserts the klass name of the object
into the arguments for the function. We do this because any function invoked
on the data manager is a constructor function that must know which klass it is constructing

name: mix
description: mix is an anonymous function that returns a new MixinBuilder for the superclass

params.name: superclass
params.description: an ES6 class definition that should be extended with mixins

return.description: An instance of MixinBuilder for the given superclass

name: MixinBuilder
description:
MixinBuilder is a class that dynamically constructs a prototype chain for the superclass
given to its constructor.

params.name: superclass
params.description: an ES6 class definition that should be extended with mixins

name: with
description:
with takes an arbitrary number of mixins as argument. A mixin is defined as follows:

(superclass) => class extends superclass {}

This definition results in an anonymous class that extends the given superclass. This way
we can reduce an array of mixins starting with this mixinBuilder's  superclass.

params.name: mixin1,mixin...,mixinN
params.description: an arbitrary number of mixins that the superclass should be extended with

return.description: this mixinBuilders superclass extended with all given mixins

name: factory
description:
The factory function constructs a new instance of an MObject with the appropriate
mixins applied to it.

params.name: klass
params.description: A string representing the klass of the managed object.

params.name: inits
params.description: An object containing initial values for the managed object

params.name: otherArg1,otherArg...,otherArgN
params.description:
Any other parameters passed to the factory are 
considered other arguments. These other arguments are passed to the constructor of the managed object 
and are meant to be used by mixins. Each mixin can then extract its required extra parameters from the otherArgs

return.description: A proxied managed object that matches the schema and implements all mixin functionality

name: DataManager
description:
The DataManager consists of a constructor that receives a schema and optionally a number of mixins as input.

The schema is parsed and for each klass a factory function is assigned to this[klassName]

Finally a proxy is wrapped around this instance of the basicRecord factory that
ensures factory.klassName(inits, args) call is forwarded to the factory function as
factory(klassName, inits, args)

params.name: schema
params.description: A raw JSON schema describing the objects that should be constructed by this data manager

params.name: mixin1,mixin...,mixinN
params.description:
an arbitrary number of mixins that should be used to extend managed
objects constructed by the basic data manager

name: mixins
description: An array of mixins for the managed objects created by this data manager

name: framework/dataManager/MObject.js
MObjectHandler
description:
MObjectHandler provides a get and a set trap for the proxy that is wrapped around a
managed object. The set trap simply invokes our custom set() function on the MObject.
get first checks whether the requested property in the object is a function. If it is
we execute that function. Otherwise, the requested property key is forwarded to our custom
get() function in the MObject

params.name: target
params.description: The target object.

params.name: propKey
params.description: The name of the property to get.

params.name: receiver
params.description: Either the proxy or an object that inherits from the proxy.

return.description: Either the value of the requested property or a function that executes the requested property

params.name: target
params.description: The target object.

params.name: propKey
params.description: The name of the property to set.

params.name: value
params.description: The value to set the property to

params.name: receiver
params.description: Either the proxy or an object that inherits from the proxy.

return.description:
true if setting the value was succesful. If setting the value failed an 
exception is thrown ny the managed object

name: MObject
description:
MObject implements the basic functionality for managed data:

It provides a set() and get() method for managed fields that will be invoked by the proxy
wrapped around this object. Managed fields are stored in the 'data' property of an MObject.

Furthermore, it provides a notifyArrayChanged() callback that will be invoekd whenever an
ArrayMField changes its state.

name: constructor
description: Constructor function for a managed object

params.name: schema
params.description: A KlassSchema describing the data property of this managed object

params.name: klass
params.description: A string representing the klass name of tihs managed object

name: proxy
description: this.proxy may only contain a pointer to the proxy wrapped around this instance of MObject

name: init
description:
Init function that initializes the data property with managed fields and sets an initial
value if this was provided in the inits parameter

params.name: inits
params.description: An object containing the initial values for this MObject

name: setThisProxy
description:
A MObject needs to know its own proxy, since we need to pass a proxied reference of the MObject 
that an MObjectMField belongs to, and non-proxied MObjects may never be interacted with except through 'this'.
So in order to ensure proper inverse relations, and MObjectMField must have a proxied reference to the object
that it belongs to. Setting the proxy must be done by the factory function.

params.name: proxy
params.description: The proxy wrapped around this MObject

throws.description: The given proxy must be the proxy wrapped around this, otherwise an error is thrown

return.description: A string representing the klass that this MObject implements

params.name: propKey
params.description: The property key of the managed field that we want to access

return.description: The value of the requested property, if it exists.

throws.description: An error is thrown if the field does not exist in this MObject's schema

params.name: propKey
params.description: The property key of the managed field that we want to access

params.name: value
params.description: The value that we want to set the managed field to

return.description: True if setting was succesfull

params.name: propKey
params.description: The property key of the field that we want to get the type of

return.description: The type of the field stored in data[propKey]

name: notifyBeforeArrayChanged
description:
By default the modification methods of managed arrays bypasses
the set trap. Because of this, arrays notify their superKlass when they change.
This way an MObject can still implement its functionality whenever an array field
is modified by extending this function.

params.name: array
params.description: The array that was modified

return.description: The property key that points to the changed array

throws.description: If no property key can be found for the changed array an error is thrown.

return.description: A string representing the managed object

name: framework/dataManager/fields/MFieldFactory.js
MFieldFactory
description:
MField is a factory function that returns one of the following managed fields
based on the given schema:
		IntegerMField
	NumberMField
	StringMField
	BooleanMField
	MObjectMField
	ArrayMField
	EnumMField
	OneOfMField

This function abstracts the MField implementation away from the user
as all outside functionality is provided by the base MField class
Note that there is one exception: The array MField, which has some additionional
Behaviour.

params.name: schema
params.description: A (partial) JSON schema that describes the field that should be constructed

params.name: superKlass
params.description: The MObject that this field belongs to

return.description: An MField that ensures its value property matches the given schema

name: framework/dataManager/fields/MFieldMulti.js
ArrayHandler
description: The ArrayHandler ensures that ArrayMfield[idx] returns ArrayMField.value[idx] when idx is an integer

params.name: target

params.name: receiver
params.description: Either the proxy or an object that inherits from the proxy.

return.description: Either the value stored at the requested index or the result of Reflect.get()

name: ArrayMField
description:
The array MField implementation is a bit different from other MField implementations.
An ArrayMField must act like a regular JavaScript array and therefore it forwards all
original ArrayMethods to the array stored within the value field and applies validation
where neccesary. When the array has been modified, the arrayHasChanged() callback is
invoked on the MObject it belongs to.


the ArrayMField always returns regular javascript values or managed objects.
the ArrayMField always takes regular javascript values as input.
the ArrayMField.value only contains objects that are instances of MFields.

params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

params.name: superKlass
params.description: The MObject that this field belongs to

name: framework/dataManager/fields/MFieldSingle.js
MField
description:
The basic MField class privides the API for data managers that
want to use the MFields values. By default we can invoke:
	
getValue		returns the internal value of the MField.
setValue		used to set the internal value of the MField.
getType			returns the type of the value stored in the MField.4
toString		returns a string representing this fields value

Each class that extends MField must provide the validate(value) function
which returns true iff the given parameter matches the schema for this MField.

params.name: type
params.description: A string representing the type of this MField

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this fields value

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be used to initialize this MField

name: type
description: String representing the type of the MField's value

name: schema
description: The schema describing this value

name: value
description: The initial value for this MField

name: setValue
description:
setValue takes a value as argument and attempts to validate this value. If it was valid we set 
this.value to the value, and otherwise we throw the error returned by the validate method

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be set in this MField

return.description: This MFields value
A string representing this MFields type
String representing this MFields value

name: NumberMField
description:
Number implementation of MField which checks the following constraints:
		
	REQUIRED:
			value 							===>	typeof(value) == typeof(Number)
	OPTIONAL:
		minimum && exclusiveMinimum 	===> 	value > minimum
		minimum 						===>	value >= minimum
		maximum && exclusiveMaximum		===>	value < maximum
		maximum 						===>	value <= maximum
		multipleOf						===>	value%multipleOf == 0

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be validated

return.description: Validate returns a boolean indicating whether the field is valid. If it is invalid an error is also returned

name: IntegerMField
description:
Integer implementation of MField which checks the following constraints:

	REQUIRED:
		value 	===>	value%1 == 0

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

name: type
description: Override NumberMFields type

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be validated

return.description: Validate returns a boolean indicating whether the field is valid. If it is invalid an error is also returned

name: StringMField
description:
String implementation of MField which checks the following constraints:

	REQUIRED:
		value 		===>	typeof(value) == typeof(String)
	OPTIONAL:
		minLength	===>	value.length >= minLength
		maxLength	===>	value.length <= maxLength
		pattern		===>	value matches pattern
		format		===>	value is one of:

									date-time
									email
									hostname
									ipv4
									ipv6
									uri

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be validated

return.description: Validate returns a boolean indicating whether the field is valid. If it is invalid an error is also returned

name: BooleanMField
description:
Integer implementation of MField which checks the following constraints:

	REQUIRED:
		value 	===>	typeof(value) == typeof(Boolean)

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be validated

return.description: Validate returns a boolean indicating whether the field is valid. If it is invalid an error is also returned

name: MObjectMField
description:
MObject implementation of MField which checks the following constraints:

	REQUIRED:
		value 	 			===>	value instanceof MObject && value.klass == schema.klass
	OPTIONAL:
		inverse		 		===>	(value[inverse] == this || value[inverse].includes(this))

params.name: schema
params.description: A JSON schema that describes this MFields value

params.name: superKlass
params.description: The MObject that this field belongs to

name: superKlass
description: The MObject that this OneOfMField belongs to

params.name: value
params.description: The value that should be validated

return.description: Validate returns a boolean indicating whether the field is valid. If it is invalid an error is also returned
